ODM party leader Raila Odinga has sent his condolences to the family of Bungoma Senator Moses Wetangula and Westlands MP Timothy Wanyonyi who lost their brother. Tony Waswa Wetang’ula who also doubled up as Wanyonyi’s aide passed on while undergoing treatment the Agha Khan Hospital, Nairobi. "My condolences go out to Senator Wetangula and Tim following the passing of their brother Tony Waswa," Raila said on Friday. "May the Lord grant their entire family comfort at this trying moment and may Tony Rest In Eternal Peace." Senate Minority Leader James Orengo also passed his condolence to his colleagues. "My colleague Senator @Wetangulam and Westlands MP @HonTimWanyonyi; my thoughts are with you and your family during this difficult time occasioned by the painful loss of your dear brother Tony Waswa. Accept my sincere condolences," he tweeted. Wetangula said the passing was a terrible tragedy to his family but they accept the gift of life that God gave him and the many years and the good time they had with him. "We have lost but that is the will of God," Wetangula said.Ford Kenya party director of communications John Mondo told the Star that Waswa had been admitted to the hospital where he succumbed to his illness.